Police are investigating a case of culpable homicide after five people died in an accident at Villa Nora in the Lephalale area yesterday (Thursday) afternoon.
Provincial Police Spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe indicated that the driver of a bakkie travelling along the R518 allegedly lost control causing the vehicle to overturn several times. The bakkie was carrying 26 persons at the time. Three died instantly while two others later succumbed to their injuries in the Lephalale District Hospital. The rest reportedly sustained injuries ranging from serious to minor.
It is alleged that they were on their way to attend a church service at Marapong outside Lephalale, according to Ngoepe. He confirmed that tree of the deceased were three women and two men and added that teir names would only be released once their next of kin had been informed of their deaths.
The exact cause of the accident is still being investigated.
